tasks.description:
Fix the memory leak in apps/admin/src/routes/__root.tsx by ensuring createQZPayBilling is never instantiated during a server-side render (AC-2.2):

- Current state: the billing instance is created inside useState(() => createQZPayBilling(...)) in RootDocument. On the server, useState lazy init runs on every request, creating a fresh instance each time.
- Fix (leading hypothesis, validated by T-006 regression test being red before this task):
  Move billing creation out of useState and into a useEffect (client-only by definition), using a useRef or useState combination:
    const billingRef = useRef<QZPayProviderProps['billing'] | null>(null);
    useEffect(() => {
      if (!billingRef.current) {
        const adapter = createHttpBillingAdapter({ apiUrl: env.VITE_API_URL });
        billingRef.current = createQZPayBilling({ ... }) as unknown as QZPayProviderProps['billing'];
      }
    }, []);
  On the server, billingRef.current will be null; QZPayProvider must accept null billing or a stub on SSR.
- Check QZPayProvider props: if billing is required and cannot be null on SSR, consider rendering QZPayProvider conditionally (only on client) or wrapping in a ClientOnly component.
- The QueryClient per-request IS the recommended TanStack SSR pattern — do NOT change it unless the T-006 regression test or the heap snapshot from T-012 proves it is the retained set. Leave a comment explaining this decision.
- Acceptance: after this change, T-006 (regression test) must pass, T-007 (guard test) must pass.

Files affected:
- apps/admin/src/routes/__root.tsx

Test requirements:
- T-006 regression test must pass (createQZPayBilling not called on each SSR render)
- T-007 guard test must pass (no createQZPayBilling in server-executed path)
- Run full admin test suite (pnpm test from apps/admin) — no regressions
